<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-11-05T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-11-05T14:00:00-05:00" n="470" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d470">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">832.01/4: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Cuba</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Guggenheim</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Habana</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-11-05T14:00:00-05:00">November 5, 1930—2
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 3:25 p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>130. President Machado informed me that Cuba desired to follow the United
                            States in its policy and any future action regarding recognition of the
                            Brazilian Government.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Guggenheim</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>